<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-07-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-07-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="805" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d805">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/23490.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Special Commissioners</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-07-01">
                                    <hi rend="italic">July 1, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>As the minutes expressly state that the agreements covered by the
                            protocols are conditional upon the establishment of a provisional <pb facs="0666" n="550" xml:id="pg_550"/> government in Mexico
                            acceptably to the contending factions, the President directs you to sign
                            the minutes stipulating in so doing that— <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>In signing these minutes the representatives of the President of
                                    the United States feel it to be their duty to declare that they
                                    do so with the express understanding that nothing contained
                                    herein is to be construed as a recognition of the government of
                                    General Huerta by the Government of the United States.</p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>